<para style="q1">

<verse number="4" style="v" />Yet their words go out over all the earth,</para>

<para style="q1">and their speech to the end of the world.</para>

<para style="q1">He has pitched a tent for the sun among them.</para>

<para style="q1">

<verse number="5" style="v" />The sun is like a bridegroom coming out of his chamber</para>

<para style="q1">and like a strong man who rejoices when he runs his race.</para>

<para style="q1">

<verse number="6" style="v" />The sun rises from the one horizon</para>

<para style="q1">and crosses the sky to the other;</para>

<para style="q1">nothing escapes its heat.</para>

